#ROOMS
#16200
Central Room~
The largest intersection of the Sewer Tunnels. The stench is overwhelming to
mortals, but is like the sweetest perfume to the Ravnos.  This seems to be the
main meeting room of the Ravnos, as there is a massive Oak table, its wood
the beautiful color that can only come with hundreds of years of care,
commanding the center of the room, with chairs of equal splendor surrounding it.
Lining the walls are shelves filled with tomes and scrolls of untold age and
knowledge.  Atop the shelves are hundreds of skulls, trophies taken by the
Ravnos after defeating a particularly worthy foe. Everything is positioned so
that the water of the sewer never touches them.  On a sideboard which matches the
table is an exquisitely cut carafe of Blood Wine which never empties, no matter
the amount poured from it, as well as goblets cut by the same masterful hands as 
the carafe.  There are candelabra on the table and sideboard filled with black 
tapers, as well as sconces along the walls, should the need for light arise.
~
