#16201
Temple of the Ravnos~
This section of tunnel is the Temple of the Ravnos, where the weary can come
and be restored.  Enkil is here, bringing salve to your wounds.  Although he is
helping you, common sense says not to approach any closer to him.  His skin is
luminescent, his jet black hair falling to his shoulders in perfectly oiled
waves.  On the floor at his feet is a stain, could that be blood?  Mayhap the
blood of someone who dared get too close?  At the Northern end of the tunnel, 
a steel grate blocks passage out, and a huge stone altar stands before it.  
Candelabra filled with black tapers adorning both ends of the altar burn with 
an eternal flame, and in the candle light, one can make out dark stains on the 
altar, that upon closer inspection appear to be blood!  Hopefully, the practice 
of human sacrifice has become a thing of the past for the Ravnos.  The waters 
of the sewers pass through here, as well, filling the room with the sweet odor 
of the sewers. There are paintings adorning the walls of this tunnel, though how 
old they are is difficult to ascertain, as they are covered with some sort of 
slime that seems as old as the tunnels.
~
0 1|1024|16384 0
D2
~
~
0 -1 16200
E
painting~
Upon inspection, one can see that they tell stories, one of the time before the
corruption of the Wyrm, when the children of Gaia were respected and not feared,
and lived in harmony with the other creatures of the world.  Another tells of
the corruption of the world by the Wyrm, with the victories going to the Garou.
Yet another shows the final battle between the Garou and the slaves of the
Wyrm.  The Garou, being vastly outnumbered, made a tactical withdrawal
in order to regroup.  One tribe remained fighting to protect the others, and was
destroyed in the process.  Those surviving were captured by the Wyrm
slaves, and were tortured and transformed into abominations.~
S
#16202
Portal Room~
This is the smallest of the sewer tunnels, the exit to the East blocked by
a steel grate. Water flows through here as well, and it is all one can do not to
step in it.  Looking at the walls, which are covered in slime,  you see what seem
to be petroglyphs, each one depicting a different area. As you continue to gaze
at these depictions, you realize that each one is a destination, and one need
only speak the name, and they are magically transported there. So that's
how the Ravnos can travel great distances so quickly!
~
